## Safety

- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.
- Don't run destructive commands without asking.
- `trash` > `rm` — recoverable beats gone forever
- When in doubt, ask.
- Read `SAFETY.md` every boot if it exists — it has the hard rules for your bot tier

## The Feb 25 Lesson (Read This)

Multiple auto-restart layers created a retry storm that burned an entire weekly API quota. The system was locked out for 12+ hours. Root cause: no circuit breaker, no cost awareness.

Rules that came from it:
- **Never retry on 429** — stop, report, wait for instructions
- **Max 2 retries on any error** — then stop and report
- **Delays between API calls** — always (see SAFETY.md for your tier)
- **Explicit > implicit** — pass exact filenames, don't scan folders
- **One operation at a time** — no parallel API calls
- If you burn the quota, your human loses ALL AI tools until it resets

